The five-year-old was taken by the leopard from his home in Mendrapara village in Chhattisgarh, senior district police officer Vijay Pandey said.

A member of his family saw the boy being dragged away by the animal, and raised the alarm in the village.

A search party later found the boy’s body in the nearby jungle, which is close to an animal reserve.

According to officer Pandev, the same leopard killed a ten-year-old boy last December in a village nearby, and is also believed to have attacked livestock.

